Barbados PM Mottley tested positive for COVID-19				




Barbados Prime Minister Mia Amor Mottley has become the latest CARICOM leader to have tested positive for COVID-19. 



Press Secretary, Roy Morris said in a statement that Mottley has a mild case and is doing well.



“The Doctors have advised that she will remain at home until they determine otherwise”.



Mottley, who is fully vaccinated, hosted a delegation from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) last week.



In the interim, Deputy Prime Minister Santia Bradshaw will perform the functions of Prime Minister.